id: pm-qcdu
title: "ADR: profile lint severity model — errors break apply, warnings flag suspicious-but-valid cross-references"
description: "Design decision for lintProjectProfile (pm-j1fj). ERRORS are conditions that make 'pm profile apply' throw or silently lose data: invalid/empty type, status, or field (normalizer throws — empty id, builtin-status override, builtin-field shadow), duplicate normalized keys within a dimension (silent last-wins upsert), unknown/invalid config knob (planConfig throws at apply), empty profile name (resolution requires it), and malformed workflow transition pairs (silently dropped by resolveTypeWorkflows). WARNINGS are authored content that is structurally valid but likely a bug: workflow.type referencing a type neither builtin nor profile-declared, workflow transitions referencing a status token (id/alias) neither builtin nor profile-declared (a dead/unreachable rule), template options.type referencing an undeclared type, non-normalized profile name (resolution folds case/hyphen but stored/display name differs), empty title/summary, and empty package spec. Warnings (not errors) for cross-references because the target type/status MAY pre-exist in the tracker independent of the profile, so erroring would create false positives against valid layered setups. assertProjectProfile throws on errorCount>0 by default; strict:true also throws on warnings for CI gates."
type: Decision
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: adr,"area:schema",living-map,pm-cli
